 South African National Parks (SANParks) recently announced that all national parks will remain closed during level 4 of the nationwide lockdown. Also read: Permits you need during lockdown level 4 and how to get it “SANParks understand that the public miss their national parks. Unfortunately, national parks remain closed despite the downgrading of lockdown restrictions to level 4,” it said. Access by all members of the public to the national parks therefore continues to be prohibited, notwithstanding the terms of Regulation 24 of the Disaster Management Act, which allow for walking, running or cycling between 06:00 and 09:00. GALLERY: Mbombela runners, cyclists and dog walkers enjoy their exercise